    Introduction

    This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

    As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

    Base URL

    http://localhost:8000

    Authenticating requests

    This API is not authenticated.

    Endpoints

    Attempt to authenticate a new session.

    Example request:
    curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost:8000/api/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"ut\",
    \"password\": \"impedit\"
}"

    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "ut",
    "password": "impedit"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
    Received response:
    Request failed with error:

    Request      

    POST api/login

    Body Parameters

    email  string  

    password  string  

    Destroy an authenticated session.

    Example request:
    curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost:8000/api/logout" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/logout"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
    Received response:
    Request failed with error:

    Get the password confirmation status.

    Example request:

    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/user/confirmed-password-status"
);

    POST api/user/confirm-password

    Return an empty response simply to trigger the storage of the CSRF cookie in the browser.

    Example request:

    --get "http://localhost:8000/api/sanctum/csrf-cookie" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
    const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost:8000/api/sanctum/csrf-cookie"

<h1><a id="user-content-about" href="#about" name="about" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a>About</h1>
<p>This Wiki is about Bookshelves project, you will find two parts covered here: the back-end part made in Laravel
which is clearly the most important part in Bookshelves and the front-end part in NuxtJS which retrieves data from
the API in order to display it in a nice user interface.</p>
<p>If you are interested in Bookshelves, you can keep only the back-end part and create your own front-end with the
technology you want. All the logic of Bookshelves is in the backend and it is even possible to not use an external
frontend and use Bookshelves with the internal backend interface.</p>
<h1><a id="user-content-demo--documentation" href="#demo--documentation" name="demo--documentation" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a>Demo &amp; documentation</h1>
<p>üöÄ <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://bookshelves.ink"><strong>bookshelves.ink</strong></a>: demo of Bookshelves<br />
üìö <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://bookshelves.ink/api/wiki"><strong>bookshelves.ink/api/wiki</strong></a>: wiki for Bookshelves usage<br />
üìö <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://bookshelves.ink/api/documentation"><strong>bookshelves.ink/api/documentation</strong></a>: API documentation</p>
<p>üìÄ <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://gitlab.com/ewilan-riviere/bookshelves-back"><strong>gitlab.com/ewilan-riviere/bookshelves-back</strong></a> : back-end of Bookshelves<br />
üé® <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://gitlab.com/ewilan-riviere/bookshelves-front"><strong>gitlab.com/ewilan-riviere/bookshelves-front</strong></a> : front-end of Bookshelves</p>
<h1><a id="user-content-i-setup" href="#i-setup" name="i-setup" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><strong>I. Setup</strong></h1>
<h2><a id="user-content-a-dependencies" href="#a-dependencies" name="a-dependencies" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><em>a. Dependencies</em></h2>
<p>Extensions for PHP, here for <code>php8.0</code></p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">sudo apt-get install -y php8.0-xml php8.0-gd
</code></pre>
<p>For spatie image optimize tools</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">sudo apt-get install -y jpegoptim optipng pngquant gifsicle webp
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-bash">npm install -g svgo
</code></pre>
<h2><a id="user-content-b-setup" href="#b-setup" name="b-setup" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><em>b. Setup</em></h2>
<p>Download dependencies</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">composer install
</code></pre>
<p>Execute <code>setup</code> and follow guide</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">php artisan setup
</code></pre>
<h1><a id="user-content-ii-generate-ebooks-data" href="#ii-generate-ebooks-data" name="ii-generate-ebooks-data" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><strong>II. Generate eBooks data</strong></h1>
<h2><a id="user-content-a-add-your-own-ebooks" href="#a-add-your-own-ebooks" name="a-add-your-own-ebooks" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><em>a. Add your own eBooks</em></h2>
<p>Add EPUB files in <code>public/storage/raw/books</code> and execute Epub Parser</p>
<blockquote>
<p><code>php artisan bookshelves:generate -h</code> to check options</p>
</blockquote>
<pre><code class="language-bash"># for fresh installation (erase current database) with force option for production
php artisan bookshelves:generate -fF
</code></pre>
<h2><a id="user-content-b-test-with-demo-ebook" href="#b-test-with-demo-ebook" name="b-test-with-demo-ebook" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><em>b. Test with demo eBook</em></h2>
<p>If you want to test Bookshelves, you can use <code>bookshelves:sample</code> to generate data from libre eBooks</p>
<blockquote>
<p><code>php artisan bookshelves:sample -h</code> to check options</p>
</blockquote>
<pre><code class="language-bash">php artisan bookshelves:sample
</code></pre>
<h1><a id="user-content-iii-tools" href="#iii-tools" name="iii-tools" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><strong>III. Tools</strong></h1>
<h2><a id="user-content-a-swagger" href="#a-swagger" name="a-swagger" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><em>a. Swagger</em></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://zircote.github.io/swagger-php/"><strong>zircote.github.io/swagger-php</strong></a>: documentation of Swagger PHP</li>
<li>
<a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://github.com/DarkaOnLine/L5-Swagger"><strong>github.com/DarkaOnLine/L5-Swagger</strong></a>: <code>darkaonline/l5-swagger</code> repository</li>
<li>
<a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://ivankolodiy.medium.com/how-to-write-swagger-documentation-for-laravel-api-tips-examples-5510fb392a94"><strong>ivankolodiy.medium.com</strong></a>: useful article about L5-Swagger</li>
<li>
<a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="http://localhost:8000/api/documentation"><strong>localhost:8000/api/documentation</strong></a>: if you use <code>php artisan serve</code>, Swagger is available on <code>/api/documentation</code>
</li>
</ul>
<p>To generate documentation from <strong>@OA</strong> comments</p>
<pre><code class="language-yml"># In dotenv
L5_SWAGGER_GENERATE_ALWAYS=true
L5_SWAGGER_BASE_PATH=/api
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-bash">php artisan l5-swagger:generate
</code></pre>
<p>To update documentation change <strong>@OA</strong> comments in controllers</p>
<pre><code class="language-php">&lt;?php

// ...

class BookController extends Controller
{
  /**
  * @OA\Get(
  *     path=&quot;/books&quot;,
  *     tags={&quot;books&quot;},
  *     summary=&quot;List of books&quot;,
  *     description=&quot;Books&quot;,
  *     @OA\Response(
  *         response=200,
  *         description=&quot;Successful operation&quot;
  *     )
  * )
  */
  public function index()
  {
    // ...
  }
}

</code></pre>
<h2><a id="user-content-b-laravel-telescope" href="#b-laravel-telescope" name="b-laravel-telescope" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><em>b. Laravel Telescope</em></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://laravel.com/docs/8.x/telescope"><strong>laravel.com/docs/8.x/telescope</strong></a>: <code>laravel/telescope</code> package doc</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Note: only useful in local</em></p>
<p>You can use <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://github.com/laravel/telescope"><strong>laravel/telescope</strong></a> on Bookshelves at <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="http://localhost:8000/telescope"><strong><a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="http://localhost:8000/telescope">http://localhost:8000/telescope</a></strong></a> if you serve project with <code>php artisan serve</code> (adapt URL if you have VHost).</p>
<p>In <strong>dotenv</strong> set <code>TELESCOPE_ENABLED</code> to <code>true</code></p>
<pre><code class="language-yml">TELESCOPE_ENABLED=true
</code></pre>
<h2><a id="user-content-c-spatie-media" href="#c-spatie-media" name="c-spatie-media" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><em>c. Spatie Media</em></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://spatie.be/docs/laravel-medialibrary/v9/introduction"><strong>spatie.be/docs/laravel-medialibrary</strong></a>: <code>spatie/laravel-medialibrary</code> package doc</li>
</ul>
<p>If you update <code>registerMediaConversions()</code> in any Model, you can regenerate conversions</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">php artisan media-library:regenerate
</code></pre>
<h2><a id="user-content-d-tests" href="#d-tests" name="d-tests" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><em>d. Tests</em></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://phpunit.de"><strong>phpunit.de</strong></a>: <code>phpunit/phpunit</code> package doc</li>
<li>
<a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://pestphp.com"><strong>pestphp.com</strong></a>: <code>pestphp/pest</code> package doc</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-bash">php artisan migrate --database=testing
</code></pre>
<p>You can run Pest and PHP Unit tests</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">php artisan pest:run
</code></pre>

<h1><a id="user-content-iv-env" href="#iv-env" name="iv-env" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><strong>IV. <code>.env</code></strong></h1>
<h2><a id="user-content-a-for-local" href="#a-for-local" name="a-for-local" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><em>a. For local</em></h2>
<pre><code class="language-yml">APP_URL=http://localhost:8000
# OR
# APP_URL=http://api.bookshelves.test

L5_SWAGGER_GENERATE_ALWAYS=true
L5_SWAGGER_BASE_PATH=/api

SANCTUM_STATEFUL_DOMAINS=localhost:3000
SESSION_DOMAIN=localhost

TELESCOPE_ENABLED=true

BOOKSHELVES_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@mail.com
BOOKSHELVES_ADMIN_PASSWORD=password
</code></pre>
<p>Setup for <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://mailtrap.io/"><strong>Mailtrap</strong></a></p>
<pre><code class="language-yml">MAIL_HOST=smtp.mailtrap.io
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USERNAME=&lt;mailtrap_username&gt;
MAIL_PASSWORD=&lt;mailtrap_password&gt;
MAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=noreply@bookshelves.ink
MAIL_FROM_NAME=&quot;${APP_NAME}&quot;
MAIL_TO_ADDRESS=contact@bookshelves.ink
MAIL_TO_NAME=&quot;${APP_NAME}&quot;
</code></pre>
<h2><a id="user-content-b-for-production" href="#b-for-production" name="b-for-production" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a><em>b. For production</em></h2>
<pre><code class="language-yml">APP_URL=https://www.mydomain.com

L5_SWAGGER_GENERATE_ALWAYS=false
L5_SWAGGER_BASE_PATH=/api

SANCTUM_STATEFUL_DOMAINS=www.mydomain.com
SESSION_DOMAIN=.mydomain.com

TELESCOPE_ENABLED=false
</code></pre>
<p>Setup for <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external-link" href="https://www.mailgun.com/"><strong>Mailgun</strong></a></p>
<blockquote>
<p>For credentials</p>
<ul>
<li>Create an account</li>
<li>After setup domain</li>
<li>Sending -&gt; Domain settings -&gt; SMTP credentials</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<pre><code class="language-yml">MAIL_HOST=smtp.eu.mailgun.org
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USERNAME=&lt;mailgun_user_login&gt;
MAIL_PASSWORD=&lt;mailgun_user_password&gt;
MAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=noreply@bookshelves.ink
MAIL_FROM_NAME=&quot;${APP_NAME}&quot;
MAIL_TO_ADDRESS=contact@bookshelves.ink
MAIL_TO_NAME=&quot;${APP_NAME}&quot;
</code></pre>
<h1><a id="user-content-v-vhost" href="#v-vhost" name="v-vhost" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a>V. <strong>VHost</strong></h1>
<h2><a id="user-content-a-nginx" href="#a-nginx" name="a-nginx" class="heading-permalink" aria-hidden="true" title="Permalink"></a>a. <em>NGINX</em></h2>
<pre><code class="language-nginx">server {
  server_name bookshelves.ink;

  error_page 500 502 503 504 /index.html;
  location = /index.html {
    root /usr/share/nginx/html;
    internal;
  }

  location / {
    include proxy_params;
    proxy_pass http://localhost:3004;
  }

  location ~ ^/(admin|api|css|media|uploads|storage|docs|packages|cache|sanctum|login|logout) {
    include proxy_params;
    proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000;
    proxy_buffer_size 128k;
    proxy_buffers 4 256k;
    proxy_busy_buffers_size 256k;
  }
}
server {
  listen 8000;
  listen [::]:8000;

  server_name bookshelves.ink;

  error_log /var/log/nginx/bookshelves.log warn;
  access_log /var/log/nginx/bookshelves.log;

  root /home/ewilan/www/bookshelves-back/public;
  index index.php;

  add_header X-Frame-Options &quot;SAMEORIGIN&quot;;
  add_header X-XSS-Protection &quot;1; mode=block&quot;;
  add_header X-Content-Type-Options &quot;nosniff&quot;;

  charset utf-8;

  location / {
    try_files $uri $uri/ /index.php?$query_string;
  }

  error_page 404 /index.php;

  location ~ ^/cache/resolve {
    try_files $uri $uri/ /index.php?$query_string;
  }

  location ~ ^/docs/ {
    try_files $uri $uri/ /index.php?$query_string;
  }

  location ~* \.(js|css|png|jpg|jpeg|gif|ico|eot|svg|ttf|woff|woff2)$ {
    expires max;
    log_not_found off;
  }

  location ~ \.php$ {
    include snippets/fastcgi-php.conf;
    fastcgi_pass unix:/run/php/php8.0-fpm.sock;
    fastcgi_buffer_size 128k;
    fastcgi_buffers 4 256k;
    fastcgi_busy_buffers_size 256k;
  }

  location ~ /\.(?!well-known).* {
    deny all;
  }
}
</code></pre>

                    clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
        </a>
